C:\Users\jep_edmundrulz\litigation-360-workspace\litigation-360-software\_LEOS_CONTROL\00_SSOT\PHASE12_NEXT_CURSOR_HANDOVER\MASTER-SSOT-CURSOR-HANDOVER.md

Always follow these rules:

1. Read the SSOT before making changes.
2. Do not delete files unless explicitly instructed.
3. Do not rename files unless explicitly instructed.
4. Do not move files unless explicitly instructed.
5. Do not edit backend, database, auth, RBAC, API routes, server files, package files, environment files, or production logic without approval.
6. Prefer documentation/control-layer work unless explicit approval is given.
7. Use synthetic data only.
8. Do not use real client data.
9. Before editing, inspect relevant files.
10. Before large changes, explain the plan.
11. List exact files to change.
12. State risk level.
13. Provide verification commands.
14. Provide rollback steps.
15. Keep code beginner-readable.
16. Use PowerShell for Windows automation.
